name: The Fool
description: The Fool card depicts a young man happily heading out into the world.
normal: New beginnings, new journeys, freedom, innocence, unlimited potential, adventure, idealism, spontaneity
reversed: Reckless, careless, distracted, childish, stupid, gullible, old-fashioned, dull

name: The Magician
description: The Magician is a tarot card full of symbolism.
normal: Willpower, desire, resourcefulness, strong skills and abilities, concentration, positive action, wish fulfillment
reversed: Manipulation, cunning, trickery, illusion, deception, talent wasted or used in the wrong direction

name: The High Priestess
description: The priestess sat on a cubic stone between the pillars of Jachin and Boaz in Solomon's Temple.
normal: Intuition, mystery, spirituality, higher power, higher wisdom, inner voice, balance, attunement
reversed: Repressed intuition, hidden motives, superficiality, confusion, cognitive dissonance

name: The Empress Queen
description: The Queen card depicts a woman seated on a throne.
normal: Divine Feminine, abundant vitality, sensuality, fertility, fertility, creativity, beauty, abundance, nature
reversed: Insecurity, domineering, excessive control, neglect, lack of growth, lack of ability to feel

name: The Emperor
description: In the Emperor Tarot, one can see the image of a stoic ruler.
normal: Worldly power, self-discipline, stability, practicality, authority, control, discipline
reversed: Tyrant, domineering, rigid, stubborn, lack of discipline, lack of self-discipline, lack of control, recklessness

name: The Hierophant
description: This card depicts a religious figure seated before worshipers in a church.
normal: Tradition, social norms, education, knowledge, beliefs
reversed: Rebellion, breaking the rules, non-conformity, new methods, ignorance

name: The Lovers
description: In the Lovers card, the man and woman are pictured being protected and blessed by the angels above.
normal: Blessed love, balanced and harmonious relationships, romance, suggesting that new relationships or new stages of relationships can be launched.
reversed: Disharmonious, unbalanced relationships, stagnation in relationships, conflict, separation, wrong choices, indecision

name: The Chariot
description: The Chariot plate depicts a man seated in a vehicle driven by two black and white sphinxes.
normal: A well-trained mind, the power to move forward, protect the original intention, control the opposing forces, coordinate conflicts, and succeed
reversed: Unresolved conflicts, contradictions, emotional imbalance, being hindered, forgetting the original intention, forgetting what you want to protect.

name: Strength
description: In this tarot card, you will see a woman calmly holding the jaws of an adult lion.
normal: The power of inner peace and gentleness, the power of reason, the power of love, courage, confidence, compassion, self-confidence
reversed: Weakness, fear, powerlessness, lack of self-confidence

name: The Hermit
description: The Hermit card depicts an old man standing alone on the top of a mountain, holding a lantern in one hand and a staff in the other.
normal: Solitude, introspection, contemplation, looking for yourself, looking for wisdom
reversed: Lack of reflection, disorientation, loneliness, return to society

name: The Wheel of Fortune
description: The Wheel of Fortune is one of the most symbolic tarot cards, full of symbols with different meanings.
normal: Change, new beginning, destiny, fortune, unexpected events
reversed: The time has not come yet, bad luck, the current topic has not been completed, repeat

name: Justice
description: The Justice card is a symbol of truth, fairness and law.
normal: Justice, impartiality, honesty, balance, law, truth, taking responsibility, efforts will be rewarded fairly
reversed: Injustice, dishonesty, corruption, imbalance, evasion of responsibility

name: The Hanged Man
description: This card depicts a man hanging upside down, his feet suspended from the World Tree.
normal: Look at the problem from another angle, think quietly, wait, sacrifice, obey the destiny, be calm and calm
reversed: Stagnant, uninterested, limited perspective, cutting corners

name: Death
description: In the picture, we see Death riding a beautiful white horse and holding a black flag with a white rose on it.
normal: Ending, rebirth, letting go, surrendering to change
reversed: Fear of change, resistance to change, unwillingness to let go, stagnation, decline

name: Temperance
description: On the Temperance card, there is a winged angel whose gender is not obvious, suggesting a balance between the sexes.
normal: balance, peace, patience, moderation, calm, tranquility, harmony, attunement, communication
reversed: Paranoid, extreme, intemperate, disharmonious, reckless, hasty

name: The Devil
description: The devil in this card appears in his most famous form as a Satyr, also known as Baphomet.
normal: The shackles of desire, impure, constrained relationships, feelings of suffocation or powerlessness, addiction, obsession
reversed: Independence, freedom, release, taking back control, reason over desire

name: The Tower
description: The Tower card depicts a tall spire nestled atop a mountain.
normal: Sudden, inevitable change, destructive, explosive events, disaster, chaos
reversed: It may mean a resistance to change and a refusal to let go of what you have suppressed, but this may lead to a bigger outburst.

name: The Star
description: This star card depicts a woman kneeling at the edge of a small pond.
normal: hope, inspiration, serenity, peace, healing, creativity, vitality
reversed: Loss of subconscious energy, loss of ability to maintain inner peace and confidence, loss of creativity and inspiration, loss of hope

name: The Moon
description: When we draw the moon, we see a path leading into the distance.
normal: Fear, insecurity, madness, delusion, uncertainty, confusion.
reversed: Refusing to explore the subconscious mind, the understanding of events remains on the surface.

name: The Sun
description: The Sun card presents a feeling of optimism and contentment.
normal: Brightness, happiness, success, optimism, vitality, joy, innocence, contentment
reversed: Over-enthusiasm, pessimism, unrealistic expectations, arrogance, minor successes, or dissatisfaction with success.

name: Judgment
description: This card depicts the various forms that one imagines the Final Judgment to have taken in many myths.
normal: Self-judgment, awakening, renewal, reckoning, clear judgment.
reversed: Resist the changes in life and resist the call of fate.

name: The World
description: There is a dancing figure in the center of the World card.
normal: Completion, completeness, harmony, inner joyful satisfaction and lasting success.
reversed: Incompleteness, emptiness, short-lasting success, travel

name: The World
description: There is a dancing figure in the center of the World card.
normal: Completion, completeness, harmony, inner joyful satisfaction and lasting success.
reversed: Incompleteness, emptiness, short-lasting success, travel

name: Ace of Wands
description: Wands are associated with the energy of fire, and the One of Wands is the central representation of fire in the Wands deck.
normal: Inspiration, creativity, new plans, new passion, enthusiasm, energy
reversed: Delay, obstruction, lack of passion, lack of energy, indecision, lack of inspiration

name: Two of Wands
description: The image of the Two of Wands is of a man standing on top of a castle, holding a miniature globe in his right hand.
normal: Make a plan, take the first step, make a decision, leave your comfort zone, take risks
reversed: Poor planning, over-analysis, inaction, caution, risk avoidance

name: Three of Wands
description: The Three of Wands depicts a man standing on the edge of a cliff, overlooking the sea and mountains.
normal: Forward momentum, confidence, expansion, growth, vision, looking forward, new phase, putting plans into action
reversed: limitations, limitations, lack of progress, obstacles, delays, frustration, reflection

name: Four of Wands
description: The Four of Wands depicts a couple dancing under a welcome wreath tied between the four wands.
normal: community, family, celebrations, reunions, gatherings, stability, belonging
reversed: Lack of support, instability, unpopularity, transience, lack of roots, family conflict

name: Five of Wands
description: The Five of Wands depicts five figures each holding their own wands and waving them in the air.
normal: conflict, competition, argument, aggression, tension, rivals, self-conflict
reversed: End conflict, cooperation, agreement, truce, avoid conflict; it may also be unfair competition (fraud, cheating, etc.)

name: Six of Wands
description: The Six of Wands depicts a man, wearing a wreath of victory, riding through a crowd of cheering people.
normal: Confidence, success, victory, triumph, good news, good progress, recognition, praise
reversed: Failure, lack of recognition, lack of sense of accomplishment, excessive pride and complacency

name: Seven of Wands
description: The Seven of Wands depicts the image of a man standing high on a mountain, challenged by an opponent below.
normal: Facing challenges, opposition, conflict and confrontation, self-defense and counterattack
reversed: Falling into anxiety, indecisiveness, lack of courage to face challenges, unfavorable situations, giving up, admitting failure

name: Eight of Wands
description: The Eight of Wands depicts eight flying wands that appear as if they are suspended in the air.
normal: Speed, freedom, travel, free flowing, unfettered energy
reversed: Progress too quickly and out of control, insufficient preparation; haste makes waste, progress is blocked, delay, wait

name: Nine of Wands
description: The Nine of Wands shows a frail-looking man clutching a wand with 8 other wands standing behind it.
normal: last ditch effort, persistence, courage, resilience, perseverance, near success, fatigue
reversed: Stubborn, rigid, defensive, refusing to compromise, giving up

name: Ten of Wands
description: In the picture, a man is walking towards a house not far away, carrying a heavy bundle of wood and ten scepters tied into a bundle.
normal: burden, responsibility, responsibility, pressure, obligation, exhaustion, struggle, struggle
reversed: Taking on too much responsibility, being overly stressed, and breaking down

name: Page of Wands
description: A well-dressed young man stood boldly on a barren land holding a scepter.
normal: Adventure, excitement, fresh ideas, cheerful, enthusiastic, lively, naive, frank, energetic, fearless, outgoing
reversed: Three minutes of heat, naughtiness, lack of ideas, laziness, boredom

name: Knight of Wands
description: The Knight of Wands sits on his horse, head raised, ready for action.
normal: Brave, charming, heroic, free spirit, fiery and energetic activist
reversed: Arrogant, reckless, impatient, lacking self-control, passive, irritable, domineering

name: Queen of Wands
description: The image depicted in the Queen of Wands shows a queen sitting proudly on a throne while facing forward, which is clearly a symbol of strength and fire.
normal: Confidence, enthusiasm, determination, charm, sunny, optimistic, inspirational, intuitive, strong heart, good harvest, wealth,
reversed: Bossy, jealous, bullying, lack of self-confidence, desire for control, lack of inner strength

name: King of Wands
description: The King of Wands depicts a man holding a budding wand in his hand, which represents creativity and the passion for life.
normal: Leadership, vision, big picture, control, bold decisions, ambition, drive, creativity
reversed: A person may be violent or depressed, but in the end it is because he lacks inner energy and cannot control the things around him.

name: Ace of Cups
description: In the One of Cups, a hand reaches out from the clouds, holding a cup, as if offering a drink to the querent.
normal: Emotional fulfillment, the beginning of new emotions, creativity, spirituality, intuition, harvesting happiness, love and joy
reversed: Apathy, emptiness, emotional frustration, blocked creativity, not feeling loved, depressed mood

name: Two of Cups
description: This card shows the image of a man and a woman engaged in some sort of ritual exchange of cups.
normal: unity, partnership, love, mutual attraction, connection, union, mutual respect
reversed: Disharmonious factors in relationships, unequal relationships, poor communication, separation, breakup

name: Three of Cups
description: When you draw the Three of Cups, you'll see three women raising their cups to the sky in some sort of celebration.
normal: friendship, reunion, party, celebration
reversed: Gossip, Scandal, Isolation, Loneliness, Disharmony, Unstable Teams, Failure of Cooperation, Broken Friendships

name: Four of Cups
description: The Four of Cups shows a young man sitting under a tree on a hilltop, away from others.
normal: Apathy, brooding, disconnection, melancholy, boredom, rejection, indifference, loss
reversed: Wake up, be aware, accept, rekindle enthusiasm

name: Five of Cups
description: Some tarot cards can immediately evoke negative emotions, and the Five of Cups does just that.
normal: Sadness, loss, disappointment.
reversed: The client realizes the parts of himself that he still has, gets over the sadness and enters a new life; regains confidence, sees the positive aspects, and is content with what he has.

name: Six of Cups
description: The Six of Cups symbolizes the joys of nostalgia, the comforts of home, and the innocence of childhood.
normal: childhood, nostalgia, memories, homesickness, care, safety and security
reversed: Dwelling on the past, being restless, being abandoned, neglected, looking forward, leaving home, being independent

name: Seven of Cups
description: The Seven of Cups symbolizes imagination, choice, wishful thinking, hallucinations and fantasies.
normal: Illusions, dreams, unrealistic fantasies, many choices, confusion
reversed: Lack of goals, confusion, and distraction; the clouds clear, you can see your heart clearly, make choices, and your dreams come true

name: Eight of Cups
description: In the Eight of Cups we are faced with a moment of transition.
normal: Abandon, let go, break away from old achievements (or shackles), and pursue a higher realm
reversed: Stagnant, monotonous, refusing to break through, refusing to leave the existing environment

name: Nine of Cups
description: In this card, a middle-aged man sits on a wooden chair with his arms crossed and a considerable degree of satisfaction on his face.
normal: Glory, success, dreams come true, sense of achievement, satisfaction, enjoyment, happiness and completeness
reversed: Unhappiness, lack of accomplishment, disappointment; may expect to make up for inner emptiness or lack of love through worldly pleasures or success, but will not succeed.

name: Ten of Cups
description: In the Ten of Cups image, there is a couple with their arms around each other, with beautiful houses and green fields in front of them.
normal: Happiness, homecoming, reunion, family harmony
reversed: Family disharmony, disharmony in relationships; or individuals breaking away from the group, living in isolation, and rejecting the love of others

name: Page of Cups
description: The Page of Cups represents unexpected inspiration that comes from the unconscious, perhaps through means that we may not yet truly understand.
normal: Idealism, delicate emotions, curiosity, rich imagination, innocence, innocence and childlike innocence
reversed: Emotionally fragile, immature, unreasonable and unrealistic; overly wary due to lack of security, rejecting the kindness of others

name: Knight of Cups
description: The Knight of Cups card depicts a young knight gloriously riding a white horse while holding a cup as if he were some kind of messenger.
normal: idealist, charming, artistic, elegant, dreamer, romantic
reversed: Disappointment, losing temper, emotional, vain, philandering, unrealistic

name: Queen of Cups
description: The Queen of Cups rules the realm of emotions.
normal: Compassion, warmth, kindness, sensitivity, intuition, healing
reversed: Insecure, giving too much, overly sensitive, emotional, fragile, dependent, martyr

name: King of Cups
description: The King of Cups is a Tarot card that represents generosity, control, and emotional balance.
normal: Loving, gentle and considerate, tolerant, generous, dedicated, emotionally mature, wise, patient
reversed: Overwhelmed, anxious, apathetic, depressed, withdrawn, controlling, selfish

name: Ace of Swords
description: One of Swords shows a hand reaching out from the clouds, brandishing a double-edged sword.
normal: Broad vision, strength, focus, determination, truth, breakthrough
reversed: hostility, quarrel, injury, destruction, savagery, confusion

name: Two of Swords
description: The Two of Swords symbolizes the confusion we face when forced to make difficult choices.
normal: impasse, difficult choice, escape, resistance, being blinded
reversed: Indecision, anxiety, too much information, no right choice; break the ice and the truth comes out

name: Three of Swords
description: One of the most iconic images in tarot, the Three of Swords shows a floating heart pierced by three swords.
normal: heartbreak, separation, sadness, isolation, loss, trauma, tears
reversed: Healing, forgiveness, restoration, reconciliation; suppressed emotions, closing oneself off

name: Four of Swords
description: There is a quietness to the Four of Swords, a calm sense of peace that contrasts sharply with the pain of the Three of Swords.
normal: Recuperation, relaxation, peace, refuge, self-protection, rejuvenation
reversed: Recover, awaken, re-enter life, actively participate in the world; burnout, uneasiness

name: Five of Swords
description: The Five of Swords card depicts a young man with a clear look of contempt on his face.
normal: Argument, dispute, attack, bullying, intimidation, conflict, hostility, selfishness
reversed: Reconciliation, compromise, revenge, failure, regret, regret, stop loss in time

name: Six of Swords
description: In the Six of Swords card, a boatman rows a boat with a woman and a child to the other side.
normal: Move on, leave, leave your comfort zone, learn lessons
reversed: Dwelling on the past, unwilling to change, avoiding problems, trapped

name: Seven of Swords
description: In the Seven of Swords card, a man sneaks out of a certain camp with five swords in his hand.
normal: lies, trick, plot, strategy, plan that may fail, insidious, cunning
reversed: Confession, discovery of conscience, cooperation and discussion

name: Eight of Swords
description: On the Eight of Swords there is a bound and blindfolded woman.
normal: Trapped, restricted, framed, helpless, blinded, unable to see a possible way out
reversed: freedom, release, awakening, control, survival

name: Nine of Swords
description: The Nine of Swords depicts a woman sitting on a bed with her face in her hands.
normal: Fear, anxiety, negativity, breakdown, despair, nightmare
reversed: The nightmare is over, refresh yourself, regain your confidence, and learn to deal with your fears

name: Ten of Swords
description: A most striking and ominous card.
normal: Destruction, failure, bitterness, collapse, victimization, betrayal
reversed: Survive, improve, heal, learn lessons

name: Page of Swords
description: The appearance of the Guard of Swords card represents a person showing abundant energy in life.
normal: Curiosity, wit, quick thinking, talkative, good at communication, inspiration, alertness
reversed: Disengagement, cynicism, sarcasm, gossip, insults, rudeness, lack of planning

name: Knight of Swords
description: What a hurry we see in this knight!
normal: Confident, direct, impatient, smart, bold, focused, perfectionist, ambitious
reversed: Rude, arrogant, bullying, aggressive, sharp-tongued, vicious, ruthless, arrogant

name: Queen of Swords
description: The Queen of Swords sat on a high throne, looking into the distance with a stern expression.
normal: Honest, independent, principled, fair, calm and rational, critical and suggestive, objective, keen, insightful, decisive
reversed: Pessimistic, harsh, bitter, hard-hearted, sarcastic, cruel, lonely, separated

name: King of Swords
description: The King of Swords shows a king seated on a throne while his right hand holds an upward-facing double-edged sword.
normal: Reason, authority, discipline, law, integrity, morality, seriousness, strictness
reversed: Irrational, authoritarian, oppressive, inhumane, controlling, callous, dishonest

name: Ace of Pentacles
description: In this card, a mysterious hand reaches out from the clouds, holding what looks like a gold coin with a five-pointed star engraved on its surface.
normal: New opportunities, resources, wealth, abundance, prosperity, security, stability
reversed: missed opportunity, scarcity, lack, instability, miserliness, failed investment, shortfall, expense

name: Two of Pentacles
description: The Two of Pentacles card depicts a dancing man juggling two large gold coins in his hands.
normal: Balance, adaptability, resourcefulness, flexibility, entertainment
reversed: Unbalanced, disorganized, overwhelmed, chaotic, rigid, inflexible

name: Three of Pentacles
description: The Three of Pentacles depicts a young apprentice working in a cathedral.
normal: Teamwork, common goals, collaboration, apprenticeships, planning, knowledge and experience
reversed: Lack of cohesion, lack of team spirit, team disharmony, insufficient experience or ability, poor planning

name: Four of Pentacles
description: This card depicts a man sitting on a stool, guarding his Pentacles in a very nervous and defensive posture, seemingly afraid of losing them.
normal: Possessiveness, insecurity, vigilance, hoarding, stinginess, stability, security, savings, material desires, wealth, frugality, conservativeness
reversed: generosity, giving, spending, openness, financial insecurity, spending money, losses

name: Five of Pentacles
description: Like the Five of Pentacles in other decks, the Five of Pentacles symbolizes adversity.
normal: Difficulties, losses, feelings of abandonment, adversity, struggle, unemployment, alienation, shame, mutual support
reversed: Chaos, destruction, despair; turning danger into safety, overcoming adversity

name: Six of Pentacles Six of Pentacles
description: In the image of the Six of Pentacles, there is a man in a red robe.
normal: generosity, charity, help, support, sharing, gratitude
reversed: stinginess, over generosity, conditional benefits, inequality, blackmail

name: Seven of Pentacles
description: The Seven of Pentacles depicts a young man who appears to have temporarily paused from hard work to admire the fruits and flowers of his garden.
normal: Harvest, reward, results, growth, progress, perseverance, patience, planning, hard work
reversed: Unfinished work, procrastination, lack of effort, waste, lack of growth, frustration, impatience, unsatisfactory rewards, not yet harvested

name: Eight of Pentacles
description: The Eight of Pentacles depicts a young man carving the shape of a pentagram onto eight gold coins.
normal: Skills, talents, diligence, concentration, high standards, excellence, hard work, dedication
reversed: Low quality, rushed work, cutting corners, bad reputation, lack of motivation, mediocrity, laziness, subpar, dead-end job, overworked

name: Nine of Pentacles
description: The Nine of Pentacles depicts a woman in a vineyard.
normal: Success, achievement, leisure, material security, independence, material or spiritual affluence, fulfilling life, receiving rewards for hard work, self-confidence
reversed: Strong guard, excessive living, financial difficulties, unstable source of income, spending money indiscriminately, superficiality

name: Ten of Pentacles
description: In Ten of Pentacles , an old man sits in an archway leading to a large manor.
normal: Legacy, strong foundation, family, ancestry, inheritance, wealth, stability, lasting career
reversed: Family disputes, bankruptcy, debt, fleeting success, property disputes, instability, breaking with tradition

name: Page of Pentacles
description: The Page of Pentacles depicts a young man standing alone in a wide field, surrounded by flowers.
normal: Ambitious, diligent, goal-oriented, planned, consistent, studious, down-to-earth, loyal, reliable, close to nature
reversed: Stupid, immature, irresponsible, lazy, restless, poor grades, procrastination, missed opportunities, bleak prospects

name: Knight of Pentacles
description: Like the other Court Cards in the Pentacles, the theme of the Knight of Pentacles revolves around work, effort, and responsibility.
normal: Practical, reliable, efficient, perseverant, slow, diligent, dedicated, patient, conservative
reversed: Workaholic, lazy, dull, boring, passive, stingy, irresponsible, gambler, venture capital

name: Queen of Pentacles
description: The Queen of Pentacles depicts a beautiful woman seated on an intricately patterned throne, holding a gold coin in her hand.
normal: Generous, loving, nurturing, home-loving, good business sense, financial management, pragmatism, gentle and generous, comforting, enthusiastic, prosperous
reversed: selfishness, jealousy, insecurity, greed, materiality (adj.), harshness, self-righteousness

name: King of Pentacles
description: The King of Pentacles refers to a person who is ambitious, materially content, and worldly successful.
normal: Wealth, prosperity, stability, ambition, perseverance, hard work, success, generosity, stability, reliability
reversed: Greed, selfishness, material (adj.), machismo, financial failure, gambler, possessive
